        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-05-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-05-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="43" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d43">
                <head>No. 43.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bounder de
                                    Melsbroeck</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-05-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 25,
                                1887</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: With reference to your note of the 21st
                            ultimo relative to the international congress of commercial law, which
                            is to be held at Brussels in September next, I have the honor to inform
                            you that David Dudley Field, esq., of New York, has been duly appointed
                            as American delegate to the congress in question.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
